The paper proposes a new method for uncertainty quantification in machine learning models, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and statistical learning (cs.SI). The paper specifically applies the method to MRI reconstruction tasks, which suggests a focus on computer vision and medical imaging, but the method itself is general and applicable to a wide range of machine learning applications.
